      "justification": "As presented, the central conclusion cannot be verified from the manuscript because the actual computed values are omitted. This is not a minor reporting gap: the paper's entire claim is a numerical coincidence at the 1e-5 level, so absent numbers mean the conclusion is unsupported by the data as presented."
    },
    {
      "finding": "Internal inconsistency in mass scheme: the paper claims all three masses in the Koide combination are MS-bar quantities, but Section 'The Observation' explicitly states that mb is held at mb(mb) while mt is held at its pole value fixed.",
      "severity": "RETRACTION-WORTHY",
      "justification": "If the calculation mixes MS-bar and pole masses in the main Koide triple, then the principal reported closure is not the stated quantity and the central conclusion is fundamentally unsupported. For a claim hinging on a tiny residual, scheme inconsistency is decisive, not cosmetic."
    },
    {
      "finding": "The treatment of renormalization scale is physically inconsistent across particles: only mc is varied with scale, while mb and mt are frozen at self-scales/pole value and inserted into the same algebraic relation.",
      "severity": "MAJOR-REVISION",
