    },
    {
      "finding": "The manuscript treats mt ambiguously between pole and MS-bar definitions, while the top mass itself is not a directly measured short-distance mass in the same sense as mc(mc) and mb(mb).",
      "severity": "MAJOR-REVISION",
      "justification": "For a precision numerical relation at the 1e-5 level, ambiguity in the top-mass definition is potentially outcome-changing. If mt is taken as a Monte Carlo or pole-like mass while the others are MS-bar running masses, the comparison is not on a controlled footing."
    },
    {
      "finding": "No quantitative uncertainty propagation is actually shown for the claimed 1e-5 closure, despite the assertion that current uncertainties dominate over the residual.",
      "severity": "MAJOR-REVISION",
      "justification": "Because all uncertainty entries are placeholders, the reader cannot assess whether the claimed minimum is meaningful, whether the μ≈mτ alignment survives correlated input variation, or whether the residual is numerically stable under standard parameter uncertainties and perturbative choices."
